<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{five^grade}} verbs form the causative by changing the final kana to the @HI{{a}}-row
and adding the suffix @HI{{saru}}. Note that ~@HI{{u}} changes to ~@HI{{wa}}.
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{ichi^grade}} verbs form the causative by dropping the final @HI{{ru}}
and adding the suffix @HI{{saseru}}.
</p>

<p>
The two irregular verbs conjugate as shown above.
</p>

<p>
All causative verbs conjugate into further forms as @KJ{{ichi^grade}} verbs.
</p>

<p>
An additional conjugation (shown here as the <em>alternative</em>) uses @HI{{su}} to form @KJ{{five^grade}} verbs.
This form generally expresses more direct causation.
</p>

